args: Take a bright-red apple and dip it in syrup.\nSee how it shines and glistens, as though\nit has become a precious treasure.

From fruit to sweet, delicious, fantastical
gemstone. All that munching and crunching
makes eating it sound just as good as it tastes.
Would you like to try a candy apple too?
This candy apple is to DIE for!
Hee hee. I'm glad you like it. Thank you\nfor teaching us such an excellent recipe.
It was the least I could do. You're always\nhelping out around the place. Wield your\nnewfound power responsibly, eh? Ha ha.

You know, I think you make them even
better than I do. You really bring out the
apples' full potential. If they could talk,
I'm sure they'd express their appreciation.
Well, since they can't, I'll do all the\nappreciating for 'em. With my face!
Please control your appetite, Luca.\nIt is time for us to return home.
Yeah, yeah. Welp, thanks, old man!\nSee ya again sometime!
Indeed. I look forward to your next visit.
We're baaaaack!\nUh, what's goin' on in here?
It seems more lively than usual.\nDid something happen?
Well, of COURSE it is more lively.\nAfter all...
We are here to find new stands for\nQuinbell's summer festival!
Could you explain what that entails,\nCatherine?
Exactly what it sounds like. This summer,\nwe've decided to ask everyone in the\nHalidom to run booths at our festival.

I am well aware of the myriad talents
possessed by the people here, and the
more personality our stands have, the
more exciting the festival will be!
Anyone who wants to apply can check\nthe requirements and talk to Natalie.\nShe'll take it from there.
Don't dump all this on me! You're the\none who has to set the dang things up.
Anyway, we're gonna do everything we\ncan to help you guys, so let's get these\napplications rollin'!
Ooh, pick me! I wanna sell shaved ice!
I want a stand that's FULL OF JUSTICE!
Hold on, one at a time! Anyone who's\napplyin' for this thing, come line up over\nhere.
That explains why everyone is so\nanimated.
Hey, Cleo! Why don't you do a candied\napple stand?
With the recipe we learned before?
Oooh, that's sure to be a smash.\nThey're a staple of every festival.
What are the requirements to apply for\na stand, Yaten?
You've gotta know what you're sellin', and\nyou've gotta have at least three people\nworkin' there.
I am indeed. It sounds like it could\nbe quite the fulfilling venture.
Hey, you want me to help out?
You're supposed to work at the orchard\nthat day, aren't you?
HOLY CRAP! I completely forgot. Maaan,\nso much for scoring an all-you-can-eat\npass on Cleo-brand candied apples...
Those are for the CUSTOMERS, Luca.\nYou attend to your previous engagements.
Now, then... I must find some willing and\nable helpers among the Halidom populace.
To think so many people have already\nagreed to help with other stands...
If only there was a pair who've yet to\nmake any plans on the day of the festival.
(Looks like she's all alone...\nThis is my chance!)
Jakob?! Wait, if you're here,\nthen that means...
We're both here for the same reason.
(We're both trying to ask Cleo out to the\nfestival!)
Did the two of you need something?\nWait... Two of you...
That's it! Are you two free on the day of\nthe festival?
Me too! My schedule's wide open!
Oh, splendid! In that case, I have\nsomething I need to ask of you.
!!!\n(Is she gonna ask ME out instead?!)
I'd love nothing more, my dear boys...\nif you could help me run a food cart!
Yes. As things are, I am short two pairs\nof hands and cannot run one alone.
O-oh... So that's all, huh? Didn't know you\nhad an interest in that sorta thing.
You cook every day, and you still want to\ndo it at a stand? Gosh, you're amazing.
Thank you. I am quite interested in\nrestaurants, you see.
Yes. When I was a child, it was my dream\nto one day open my own eatery.
I do not dislike my current job, mind you;\nI merely thought running a food cart might\ncross an item off my bucket list.
So you wanted to be a restaurateur?\nThat's kind of a surprise. Why'd you\nbecome a servant instead, then?
I had my reasons at the time.

I know it's a bit silly, thinking of childhood
dreams after all this time. Yet, I now have
a chance to make that dream come true,
so I'd like to strive for it with all my might.
(If I decide to take this on, it'll mean I\ncan't go on a date with Cleo. But...)
(She said this was her dream.\nHow could I possibly refuse?!)
Okay. If you're in, then I'm in.
Me too. We're gonna make this food cart\nthe one to beat!
Jakob... Rodrigo... Thank you so much!
The stand is up, our ingredients are\nready, and my yukata has nary a wrinkle.\nPreparations are at last complete.
